BP &= \frac{3}{\sqrt{1 - t}} \sqrt{1 - \frac{27}{8 + 8x^2}}, \\
CP &= \frac{3}{\sqrt{1 - t}} \sqrt{\frac{27}{8 + 8x^2}}, \\
PQ &= \frac{3}{\sqrt{1 - t}} \cdot \frac{x}{\sqrt{1 + t}}, \\
x^2 &= BP^2 + PQ^2 - 2 BP \cdot PQ \cos \beta + BQ^2 \\
&= \frac{27}{8 + 8x^2} + \frac{9x^2}{1 + t} - 2 \cdot \frac{3}{\sqrt{1 - t}} \cdot \frac{x}{\sqrt{1 + t}} \cdot \frac{1}{2} \cdot \sqrt{1 - t} + \frac{27}{8 + 8x^2}, \\
x^2 &= CP^2 + PQ^2 - 2 CP \cdot PQ \cos \gamma + CQ^2 \\
&= \frac{27}{8 + 8x^2} + \frac{9x^2}{1 + t} - 2 \cdot \frac{3}{\sqrt{1 - t}} \cdot \frac{x}{\sqrt{1 + t}} \cdot \frac{1}{2} \cdot \sqrt{1 - t} + \frac{27}{8 + 8x^2}.
\end{align*}Adding these equations, we get
\[2x^2 = \frac{54}{8 + 8x^2} + \frac{18x^2}{1 + t} - 3x \sqrt{1 - t} + \frac{54}{8 + 8x^2}.\]Then
\[4x^2 + 2x^2 t = 27 + 9x^2 - 6x \sqrt{1 - t}.\]By the Law of Cosines on triangle $APS,$
\begin{align*}
AP^2 &= PS^2 + AS^2 - 2 PS \cdot AS \cos \delta \\
&= 9 + x^2 - 6x \cos \delta.
\end{align*}Then
\begin{align*}
\cos \delta &= \frac{9 + x^2 - AP^2}{6x} \\
&= \frac{9 + x^2 - \frac{9}{\sin^2 \alpha}}{6x} \\
&= \frac{9 + x^2 - \frac{9}{t}}{6x} \\
&= \frac{9 + x^2 - \frac{243}{8 + 8x^2}}{6x}.
\end{align*}By the Law of Cosines on triangle $BPC,$
\begin{align*}
x^2 &= BP^2 + CP^2 - 2 BP \cdot CP \cos (\phi - \theta) \\
&= \frac{27}{8 + 8x^2} + \frac{27}{8 + 8x^2} - 2 \cdot \frac{3}{\sqrt{1 - t}} \cdot \frac{3}{\sqrt{1 - t}} \cos (\phi - \theta) \\
&= \frac{54}{8 + 8x^2} - \frac{18}{1 - t} \cos (\phi - \theta).
\end{align*}Then
\begin{align*}
\cos (\phi - \theta) &= \frac{18}{\frac{8}{x^2} + 8} \\
&= \frac{9x^2}{4 + 4x^2}.
\end{align*}Then
\begin{align*}
\cos \delta &= \frac{9 + x^2 - \frac{243}{8 + 8x^2}}{6x} \\
&= \frac{9 + x^2 - \frac{27}{x^2 + 1}}{6x} \\
&= \frac{9x^4 + 9x^2 - 27}{6x(x^2 + 1)} \\
&= \frac{3x^2 - 3}{2(x^2 + 1)} \\
&= \frac{3(x^2 - 1)}{2(x^2 + 1)}.
\end{align*}Then
\[6x \cos \delta = 3x^2 - 3.\]Hence,
\[4x^2 + 2x^2 t = 27 + 9x^2 - 2(3x^2 - 3) = 33 - x^2.\]Solving, we find $x^2 = \frac{33}{5},$ so $x = \boxed{\frac{\sqrt{165}}{5}}.$

