Let $K$ be the projection of $A$ onto $BC.$  Then $AK = 5,$ so $HK = 5 - BM = \frac{5 \sqrt{2}}{2}.$  Also, $HN = \frac{5 \sqrt{2}}{4}.$

Then $PN = \frac{5 \sqrt{2}}{4 \cos B} = \frac{5 \sqrt{2}}{2},$ so $PD = \frac{5 \sqrt{2}}{2} - \frac{5}{\sqrt{2}} = \frac{5 \sqrt{2}}{2} - \frac{5 \sqrt{2}}{2} = 0.$  Hence, $P$ lies on $AD,$ and $AP = AD = 10.$

